## Setup Instructions

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
cd ecommerce-frontend
npm install
```

### 2. Start development server

```bash
npm run dev
```

App runs at → http://localhost:3000

> The Vite proxy forwards all `/api` requests to `http://localhost:5000` (your backend).
> The frontend works standalone with demo data even before the backend is connected.

---

## Role-Based Access

| Role  | Login URL | After Login       |
|-------|-----------|-------------------|
| User  | /login    | → Home page (/)   |
| Admin | /login    | → /admin dashboard|

The admin role is determined by the `role` field in the JWT payload returned by the backend.
The frontend route guard (`AdminRoute`) rejects any user whose `role !== 'admin'`.

---

## Environment

No `.env` file needed for the frontend.
All API calls go through the Vite proxy (`/api` → `localhost:5000`).

When deploying to Vercel (production):
- Set `VITE_API_URL` in Vercel dashboard
- Update `api.js` baseURL to `import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL`

